  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dc5\u0db3\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dc0 \u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The student wearing the knee shoe leaves the hospital",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The director of Lady Ridgeway Children's Hospital, Colombo Dr. Wijesuriya said.",
        "The director also mentioned that after the tests confirmed that the child's body had not been poisoned, he was discharged from the hospital.",
        "However, the doctor who examined the child found two signs that the child had been bitten by a snake, and said that the child was wearing a pair of socks so that the snake's venomous fangs might not have happened.",
        "A thirteen-year-old student of a main school in Colombo faced this incident last (23rd).",
        "The student who wore the shoe with the snake was coming to school from his home in Kadawata, when he felt that something was moving inside the shoe and when he came to school and took off the shoe to check, he found this snake.",
        "After that, the college teachers took steps to admit the child to Lady Ridgeway Children's Hospital, Colombo.",
        "The director of the hospital added that such accidents can be avoided by putting shoes in bags and tying them at a high place to avoid leaving the shoes of everyone, including children, outside the house."
      ],
